@node Introduction "1. Introduction"

                               @{fg highlight}1. Introdution
                               ==============@{fg text}


   You have made us very happy.  First, because of your choice of Diavolo
Backup.  But mainly, because you are bothering to read this documentation.

   Although Diavolo is almost self-explaining, we @{b}highly recommend@{ub}
that you read through this document a little.  You will find that Diavolo
Backup can offer You much more than you would normally notice at first.

   You should also know why, alone your choice of this program, was the
correct purchase.  And lastly, we are sure you would like to know how to
convince your skeptical friends..

Features that make Diavolo Backup one of a kind:

     Extremely high speed (up to @{b}2 MB@{ub} per minute to disks, up to @{b}15 MB@{ub} per
     minute to SCSI streamer (DAT) )

     Efficient @{b}Data compression@{ub} through using @{b}XPK-Libraries@{ub}: Possibility
     of using different developed (current and future) packing algorithms
     simply with the click of your mouse.

     @{b}SCSI-Streamer@{ub} support. Configurable to make use of the additional
     features of advanced devices like @{b}DAT-Streamer@{ub}.

     Support of @{b}changeable hard drives@{ub} (such as @{b}SyQuest@{ub} Drives)

     Parallel usage of @{b}High Density@{ub} diskettes (HD, 1.76 MB cap.) together
     with Normal Density diskettes (DD, 880 KB cap.) in one backup (A High
     Density drive from Commodore is required for this option).

     @{b}Data Encryption@{ub} possible with up to a 10 letter password.

     Backups of @{b}different partitions@{ub} or hard drives @{b}simultaneously@{ub} in one
     session.

     Clear and easy to understand @{b}user-interface@{ub} (localized to @{b}German@{ub} or
     @{b}English@{ub}, other languages will follow).

     All steps are optically clear and allow for a quick summary of all
     actions.

     Full @{b}multi-assign@{ub} (Multiple directories with one logical name)
     support.

     Support of @{b}Hard and Softlinks@{ub}.  The links can be symbolically saved
     and restored (that is if the links are the same by restoring as they
     were when saved).


