@node Data-Choice "6. Data Choice"

                               @{fg highlight}6. Data Choice
                               ==============@{fg text}


   In the previous chapters, the options to the choice of data was not
covered in detail.  Usually, the simple options are all that is required.
However, now and then you will need more in-depth options.  Other than that,
the choice of data can be completely controlled using the keyboard which
will also be covered in this chapter.

   @{fg highlight}To refresh your memory@{fg text}:

   The left window displays the directories of the hard drive chosen, and
the right window displays all the data from the active / selected directory.

   You can scroll the window in any direction with the arrow keys.  The
Tabulator key switches between the two windows (Using Alt + Arrow key left
and Alt + Arrow key right also does this).

  To select directories or data, you can either Double-click, Shift + single
click, press the Space key, or the Return key.  If you select data with the
Space key or the Return key, then the cursor will automatically jump to the
next entry.  That way, you can select many entries with one press of the
key.  It is best if you just try it out.

