@node Priorities "Priorities"

                                 @{fg highlight}Priorities@{fg text}


   While a making a @{" backup " link Saving-with-Diavolo}, @{" comparing " link Comparing-Backups}, or @{" restoring " link Restoring-Software}, Diavolo
backup starts three sub-tasks.

   This way, The data can be simultaneously be read, packed, and written.
This brings a higher speed advantage to Diavolo Backup.

   In these three fields, you change the three sub-task priorities in the
Amiga-system. The priority 0 should be adjusted for all tasks to be treated
equally.

   When saving to diskettes, change the priority of the Disk-/Streamertask
to 1 to reach maximal speed.

   In all other cases, setting all three priorities to 0 has proven to be
the optimal setting.


