@node Data-compression-and-encryption "Data compression and encryption"

                      @{fg highlight}Data compression and encryption@{fg text}


   Diavolo Backup uses the XPK-library for it's compression and data
encryption.  It is known not only for it's high speed and efficiency, but above
all, through it's flexibility.  The library can, at any time, be expanded with
new packing algorithms as they become available.  You can install these
packers yourself.  Other than that, you already have now a large assortment
of different packers.

   Data that are already packed, or those that are smaller than 500 bytes,
will generally not be compressed.

   Diavolo Backup has four pre-defined adjustments that you can choose from
without having to have background knowledge of the XPK-libraries.

   The very first option, "No compression" is self explanatory.  It should
be used when
  - saving to a very fast backup medium, like SCSI DAT-Streamer,
  - saving to a device with a built-in hardware compression or
  - saving already compressed data.

   The second option should be used for the Amiga 500/600/1000/2000 which do
not have an accelerator card.  This is a fast, but very useful option that,
even with limited calculations, brings good results.

   The third option should be used for faster computers such as the Amiga
1200.  The compression percentage is a bit better, and the processing power
of the computer is used.

   The Fourth option called "Slow/High eff." should be used for high-end
computers such as the Amiga 3000/4000 or those computers having an
accelerator card.  The compressor used is clearly slow, but the data is
packed efficiently better.  And on a fast computer, it is worth using.

   The fifth option is the "Data encryption Algorithm".  This is
automatically used when a password is entered.

   With each of these options, a certain packer has been chosen from the XPK-
library.  If you have not yet changed the standard options, then the packers
should reflect their settings of being fast/medium/slow, respectively.

   You have, of course, the possibility of changing the adjustments.  For
example, you could change the packer being used, or choose a completely new
packer.  However, you should understand the concept of the XPK-library
thoroughly.  You can find the complete XPK-library package on your Diavolo
Backup program diskette which has in-depth information about the different
compressors.

   To change the arrangement of the packers, press the respective "Change"
button.

   All installed compressor algorithms are represented here.  In the field
on the right, you see information explaining the currently selected packer.

   The sliding bar gadget under "Efficiency" is only supported by some of
the packers.  You can tell if the packer supports this option by moving the
slider.  If the information explaining the packer changes, then the slider
is supported.  To get more information concerning the effect and efficiency
of each packer, please read through the accompanying XPK documentation.

   Also, please keep in mind that the compression and speed ratio displayed
are directly affected by the computer system being used and should only be
considered for comparison between the different packers themselves.


