@node Problems-&-Solutions "13. Troubleshooting"

                            @{fg highlight}13. Troubleshooting
                            ===================@{fg text}



   This chapter contains a collection of the more common problems, that our
customers have encountered.

   Almost all of these problems can be easily handled.

   You should read this text before turning to the different support
possibilities.


  @{b}PROBLEM:@{ub}
               When restoring / comparing a backup that was made using an
               older version of Diavolo, an error "XPK Mistake:  File not
               compressed" or "Diavolo Unpacker:  WriteCursor !-
               EndOfFileMark" is shown.

  @{b}SOLUTION:@{ub}
               This is a bug that slipped through in the 1.12 Version.  To
               restore this data, start Diavolo from CLI with the option
               "NOUNPACK" Example:  Diavolo exists in the directory
               Work:Diavolo.  You would then enter the following in the CLI:

               CD work:Diavolo
               Diavolo NOUNPACK

               Try once again to restore the backup.  This will usually take
               care of this problem.


  @{b}PROBLEM:@{ub}
               With two or more High Density floppy drives the second drive
               does not recognize a High Density floppy as it should.

  @{b}SOLUTION:@{ub}
               This is a hardware problem from the HD floppy drive.  It is
               impossible for the Amiga to recognize HD diskettes while
               reading or writing simultaneously to another floppy drive.
               To get around this problem, do not insert the a disk until
               the other floppy drive has finished reading or writing.


  @{b}PROBLEM:@{ub}
               An encrypted backup can not be restored even with the correct
               password.

  @{b}SOLUTION:@{ub}
               You have probably entered an ODD (not even) number in the XPK
               algorithm "FEAL" (the standard is 8).  In older versions of
               this library this algorithm had a bug that does not allow
               backups with un-even numbers to be restored.

               There is no way of restoring the data. You should update the
               library to the current version (which is included in the
               Diavolo package)


  @{b}PROBLEM:@{ub}
               Various XPK errors are shown when saving or restoring data.

  @{b}SOLUTION:@{ub}
               The XPK libraries can only be used by one program at a time.
               Programs that increase your harddrive capacity like
               "DiskExpander" and "XFH" also use XPK to pack data.  Make
               sure these type of programs are deactivated before using
               Diavolo.  You can save a harddrive that has been packed
               without problems.


  @{b}PROBLEM:@{ub}
               The Streamer can not be communicated with.  The function
               "Inquiry" does not react when selected.

  @{b}SOLUTION:@{ub}
               This problem is not so easily remedied.  The following
               mistakes could exist:

               - You have entered the wrong Device name.  Check with the
                 manufacturer of your controller for the correct Device
                 name, or read Chapter @{" 10.1 Streamer configuration " Link SStreamer-configuration}.

               - You have entered the wrong Unit number.  Try all numbers
                 from 0 to 6.

               - Your SCSI Bus has been incorrectly configured.  Get advice
                 from an authorized dealer or business to take care of this
                 problem.


  @{b}PROBLEM:@{ub}
               The Streamer is recognized and correctly displayed by
               Diavolo.  The function "Check capabilities" is incorrectly
               done.  Diavolo exits with an error or the computer simply
               locks up.

  @{b}SOLUTION:@{ub}
               If the harddrive light stays on without blinking, then there
               is the possibility that the SCSI Bus is not correctly
               functioning.  Your only chance is most likely an authorized
               Repairman.

               There could also be an incompatibility problem with the
               Streamer or the Controller.  In the case, contact us.


  @{b}PROBLEM:@{ub}
               While saving/comparing/restoring to a Streamer tape or a
               file, the computer locks up and/or the harddrive light burns
               constantly.

  @{b}SOLUTION:@{ub}
               You seem to have a Reselection problem.  Please read Chapter
               @{" 10.8 SCSI Reselection " Link SSCSI-Reselection}.  As a rule, the manufacturer may be
               able to assist you.


  @{b}PROBLEM:@{ub}
               While making a backup, Diavolo reported no errors, but the
               program can not find the backup on the tape when restoring.

  @{b}SOLUTION:@{ub}
               Try making a backup WITHOUT the options "Setmarks" and
               "Direct seek".


  @{b}PROBLEM:@{ub}
               Diavolo has correctly written to more than one Streamer tape,
               but can no longer read the tape completely.  The Error
               "End of Media reported to early" is shown.

  @{b}SOLUTION:@{ub}
               It is no longer possible for your streamer to read the data
               that it has written.  Consequently, you can not reliably make
               multiple tape backups.

               You can, however, recover most of the data.  After Diavolo
               reports an error, you can then use the filelist option to see
               which files were successfully restored.  Repeat the restore
               with the difference of deselecting those files that have been
               restored.  Also, you should de-select the first files that
               are within first 20 KB of the second tape to be sure that
               Diavolo begins with this tape.


If your problems cannot be solved, then please send a Report to one of the
addresses listed in chapter @{" 12. Support Information " link Support}.



